<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="454" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1402,1678]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,385,1402,1427]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">Material examined.</emphasis>
This species was found at all sampled sites. Vouchers were collected from the Islas Marietas with two males (ICMyL MAZ 
<number box="[499,556,1438,1462]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" value="9028.0">9028</number>
A) and two females (ICMyL MAZ 
<number box="[953,1014,1438,1462]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" value="9028.0">9028</number>
B); as well at Estacahuite, close to the Huatulco region, with one male (ICMyL MAZ 
<number box="[681,738,1474,1498]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" value="9037.0">9037</number>
A) and five females (ICMyL MAZ 
<number box="[1135,1196,1474,1498]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" value="9037.0">9037</number>
B).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="454" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1402,1678]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1511,1535]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is commensal on pocilloporid corals and has a wide distribution along the Pacific Ocean and Red Sea (Wicksten &amp; Hendrickx 
<number box="[663,724,1546,1570]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" value="2003.0">2003</number>
). In Mexican waters, 
<taxonomicName box="[972,1072,1547,1571]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Alpheus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lottini">
<emphasis box="[972,1072,1547,1571]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">A. lottini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was noticed as far north as 
<collectingCountry box="[1395,1435,1546,1570]" name="Iceland" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">Isla</collectingCountry>
Coronados (
<geoCoordinate box="[293,392,1582,1606]" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" precision="925" value="26.1">
<number box="[293,323,1582,1606]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" value="26.0">26</number>
°06´N
</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[409,525,1582,1606]" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" precision="925" value="-111.26667">
<number box="[409,450,1582,1606]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" value="111.0">111</number>
° 
<number box="[460,488,1582,1606]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" value="16.0">16</number>
´W
</geoCoordinate>
) in the Loreto area on 
<taxonomicName box="[812,946,1582,1606]" class="Anthozoa" family="Pocilloporidae" genus="Pocillopora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scleractinia" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[812,946,1582,1606]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">Pocillopora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
corals (Hernández 
<emphasis box="[1179,1241,1582,1607]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[1252,1312,1582,1606]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" value="2009.0">2009</number>
), in Bahía Santiago, and in the Huatulco region (Hermoso, 
<number box="[711,771,1618,1642]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" value="1999.0">1999</number>
). In our study, the species was recorded from all sampled sites along the Mexican tropical Pacific coast.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
